g a better job than the' b'other algorithms, but slower".' b'' b"there's also an implementation of:" b'' b'wan, wong, and prusinkiewicz, _an algorithm for multidimensional data' b'clustering_, transactions on mathematical software, vol. (june, b'pp. b'' b'avialable as princeton.edu:pub/graphics/colorquant.shar. this code,' b'in modified form, appears in the utah raster toolkit as well.' b'' b'' b'4) converting color into grayscale.' b'' b'the ntsc formula is:' b'' b'luminosity red green blue' b'' b'' b'5) quantizing grayscale to black&white.' b'' b'the only reference you need for this stuff is:' b'' b'digital halftoning, robert ulichney, mit press isbn b'' b'but before you go off and start coding, check out the image manipulation' b'software mentioned in item below. all of the packages mentioned can do' b'some form of gray to b&w conversion.' b'' b'' b'6) rotating a raster image by an arbitrary angle.' b'' b'the obvious but wrong method is to loop over the pixels in the source' b'image, transform each coordinate, and copy the pixel to the destination.' b'this is wrong because it leaves holes in the destination. instead,' b'loop over the pixels in the destination image, apply the *reverse*' b'transformation to the coordinates, and copy that pixel from the source.' b'this method is quite general, and can be used for any one-to-one' b'2-d mapping, not just rotation. you can add anti-aliasing by doing' b'sub-pixel sampling.' b'' b'however, there is a much faster method, with antialising included,' b'which involves doing three shear operations. the method was originally' b'created for the im raster toolkit (see below); an implementation is' b'also present in pbmplus. reference: "a fast algorithm for raster' b"interface (vancouver). an article on the im toolkit appears in" b'the same journal. an updated version of the rotation paper appears' b'in "graphics gems" (see section under the original title.' b'' b'' b'7) free image manipulation software.' b'' b'there are a number of toolkits for converting from one image format to' b'another, doing simple image manipulations such as size scaling, plus' b'the above-mentioned color gray, gray b&w conversions.' b'here are pointers to some of them:' b'' b'xv by john bradley. x-based image display, manipulation, and format' b'conversion package. xv displays many image formats and permits editing' b'of gif files, among others. the program was updated see the file' b'contrib/xv-2.21.tar.z on export.lcs.mit.edu.' b'' b'pbmplus, by jef poskanzer. comprehensive format conversion and image' b'manipulation package. the latest version is always available via' b'anonymous ftp as ftp.ee.lbl.gov:pbmplus*.tar.z,' b'wuarchive.wustl.edu:graphics/graphics/packages/pbmplus/pbmplus*.tar.z,' b'and export.lcs.mit.edu:contrib/pbmplus*.tar.z.' b'' b'provides a portable and efficient format and related toolkit. the' b'format is versatile in supporting pixels of arbitrary channels,' b'components, and bit precisions while allowing compression and machine' b'byte-order independence. the kit contains more than tools with' b'extensive support of image manipulation, digital halftoning and format' b'conversion. previously distributed on tape c/o the university of' b'waterloo, an ftp version will appear someday.' b'' b'utah rle toolkit. conversion and manipulation package, similar to' b'pbmplus. available via ftp as cs.utah.edu:pub/urt-*,' b'princeton.edu:pub/graphics/urt-*, and freebie.engin.umich.edu:pub/urt-*.' b'' b'conversion and manipulation package, similar to pbmplus. version b'available via ftp as nl.cs.cmu.edu:/usr/mlm/ftp/fbm.tar.z,' b'ftp.uu.net:pub/fbm.tar.z, and ucsd.edu:graphics/fbm.tar.z.' b'' b'writes its own image format, displays on an x11 screen, and does some' b'image manipulations. version is available via ftp as' b'export.lcs.mit.edu:contrib/img_1.3.tar.z, and' b'venera.isi.edu:pub/img_1.3.tar.z along with a large collection of color' b'images.' b'' b'xim, x image manipulator, by philip r. thompson. it does essential' b'interactive image manipulations and uses x11r4 and the osf/motif toolkit' b'for the interface. it supports images in and bit formats.' b'reads/writes and converts to/from gif, xwd, xbm, tiff, rle, xim, and' b'other formats. writes level postscript. other utilities and image' b'application library are included. not a paint package. available via' b'ftp from gis.mit.edu.' b'' b'formats and displays them on an x11 screen. available via ftp as' b'export.lcs.mit.edu:contrib/xloadimage*, and in your nearest comp.sources.x' b'archive.' b'' b'xli, by grame gill, is an updated xloadimage with numerous improvements' b'in both speed and in the number of formats supported. available in the' b'same places as xloadimage (contrib tape, comp.sources.x archives).' b'' b'portable library for reading and writing tiff files, plus a few tools' b'for manipulating them and reading other formats. available via ftp as' b'ucbvax.berkeley.edu:pub/tiff/*.tar.z or ftp.uu.net:graphics/tiff.tar.z' b'' b'xtiff, an x11 tool for viewing a tiff file. it was written to handle' b'as many different kinds of tiff files as possible while remaining' b'simple, portable and efficient. xtiff illustrates some common problems' b'with building pixmaps and using different visual classes. it is' b"distributed as part of sam leffler's libtiff package and it is also" b'available on export.lcs.mit.edu, ftp.uu.net and comp.sources.x.' b'xtiff was announced in it includes xlib and xt versions.' b'' b'alv, a sun-specific image toolkit. version posted to' b'comp.sources.sun on 11dec89. also available via email to' b'' b'popi, an image manipulation language. version posted to' b'comp.sources.misc on 12dec89.' b'' b'imagemagick, an x11 package for display and interactive manipulation' b'of images. includes tools for image conversion, annotation, compositing,' b'animation, and creating montages. imagemagick can read and write many of' b'the more popular image formats. available via ftp as' b'export.lcs.mit.edu:contrib/imagemagick.tar.z.' b'' b'khoros, a huge meg) graphical development environment based on' b'x11r4. khoros components include a visual programming language, code' b'generators for extending the visual language and adding new application' b'packages to the system, an interactive user interface editor, an' b'interactive image display package, an extensive library of image and' b'signal processing routines, and 2d/3d plotting packages. available via' b'ftp as pprg.eece.unm.edu:pub/khoros/*.' b'' b'laboimage, a sunview-based image processing and analysis package. it' b'includes more than image manipulation, processing and measurement' b'routines, on-line help, plus tools such as an image editor, a color' b'table editor and several biomedical utilities. available via anonymous' b'ftp as ads.com:pub/vision-list-archive/shareware/laboimage_3.1.tar.z' b'' b'the san diego supercomputer center image tools, software tools for' b'reading, writing, and manipulating raster images. binaries for some' b'machines available via anonymous ftp in sdsc.edu:sdscpub.' b'' b'the independent jpeg group has written a package for reading and' b'writing jpeg files. ftp to ftp.uu.net:graphics/jpeg/jpegsrc.v?.tar.z' b'' b"don't forget to set binary mode when you ftp tar files. for you milnet" b"folks who still don't have name servers, the ip addresses are:" b'' b'ads.com\t\t\t128.229.30.16' b'cs.utah.edu\t\t\t128.110.4.21' b'coral.cs.jcu.edu.au\t\t137.219.17.4' b'export.lcs.mit.edu\t\t18.24.0.12' b'freebie.engin.umich.edu\t141.212.103.21' b'ftp.ee.lbl.gov\t\t128.3.112.20' b'ftp.uu.net\t\t\t137.39.1.9 or b'gis.mit.edu\t\t\t18.80.1.118' b'gondwana.ecr.mu.oz.au\t128.250.70.62' b'karazm.math.uh.edu\t\t129.7.7.6' b'marsh.cs.curtin.edu.au\t134.7.1.1' b'nic.funet.fir\t\t128.214.6.100' b'ftp.ncsa.uiuc.edu\t\t141.142.20.50' b'nl.cs.cmu.edu\t\t128.2.222.56' b'pit-manager.mit.edu\t\t18.172.1.27' b'pprg.eece.unm.edu\t\t129.24.24.10' b'princeton.edu\t\t128.112.128.1' b'sdsc.edu\t\t\t132.249.20.