musg88.ps.z' b'' b'an implementation of this paper may be found in rayshade.' b'' b'another paper exists:' b'' b'%a david w. paglieroni' b'%a sidney m. petersen' b'%t parametric height field ray tracing' b"%j proceedings of graphics interface b'%i canadian information processing society' b'%c toronto, ontario' b'%d may b'%p b'' b'and still one more:' b'' b'musgrave, kolb, and mace' b'"the synthesis and rendering of eroded fractal terrains",' b"computer graphics vol no. (siggraph procedings) p. b'' b'' b'' b'24) how to find the area of a 3d polygon' b'' b'the area of a triangle is given by (in c notation),' b'' b'area x[0] y[1] x[1] y[2] x[2] y[0] b'( x[1] y[0] x[2] y[1] x[0] y[2] b'' b'and the area of a planar polygon is given by' b'' b'area b'' b'for i i n i++ b'area x[i] y[i x[i y[i] b'area x[n y[0] x[0] y[n b'area b'' b'if the area is a negative number, the polygon or triangle is' b'clockwise, if positive, it is counterclockwise.' b'' b'from ronald golman\'s gem (in graphics gems ii see section above), "area' b'of planar polygons and volume of polyhedra:"' b'' b'the area of a polygon p0, p1, p2, pn, not in the x-y plane, is' b'given by' b'' b'area(polygon) n sigma pk x pk+1 b'' b'where n is the unit vector normal to the plane and p is a polygonal' b'vertex. the represents the dot product operator and the x' b'represents the cross product operator. sigma represents the summation' b'operator. represents the absolute value operator. pn+1 is equal' b'to p0.' b'' b'' b'25) how to join acm/siggraph' b'' b'probably the easiest way to join acm/siggraph is to trot over to your' b'local technical library and find a copy of communications of the acm.' b'somewhere within the first few pages will be an application blank.' b'fill it out and mail it in. acm membership for students costs b'voting or associate membership (yearly)' b'' b'siggraph student membership costs an additional for' b'voting or associate members (also yearly). to get tog (transactions' b"on graphics) it's another for students and for voting or" b'associate members.' b'' b"if you just want to join siggraph without joining acm, it'll cost you" b'$59.00 (no student discount).' b'' b'there are surcharges for overseas airmailing of publications.' b'' b'their phone number is fax number b'snailmail address:' b'' b'acm' b'po box b'church street station' b'new york, new york b'' b'siggraph will be held in anaheim, california, at the anaheim' b'convention center (just up the street from disneyland) on august b'' b'26) where can i find mri and ct scan volume data?' b'' b'volume data sets are available from the university of north carolina at' b'omicron.cs.unc.edu in /pub/softlab/chvrtd. (commerical' b'use is prohibited.)' b'' b'head data a 109-slice mri data set of a human head.' b'' b'knee data a 127-slice mri data set of a human knee.' b'' b'hipip data the result of a quantum mechanical calculation of a sod data' b'of a one-electron orbital of hipip, an iron protein.' b'' b'sod data an electron density map of the active site of sod (superoxide' b'dismutase).' b'' b'ct cadaver head data a 113-slice mri data set of a ct study of a cadaver' b'head.' b'' b'mr brain data a 109-slice mri data set of a head with skull partially' b'removed to reveal brain.' b'' b'rna data an electron density map for staphylococcus aureus ribonuclease.' b'' b'' b'27) specific references on spatial data structures including quadtrees' b'and octrees' b'' b'h. samet,' b'the design and analysis of spatial data structures,' b'addison-wesley, reading, ma, b'isbn b'' b'h. samet,' b'applications of spatial data structures: computer graphics, image processing, a' b'nd gis,' b'addison-wesley, reading, ma, b'isbn b'' b'' b'28) where can i get a program to plot xy(z) data or f(x) data?' b'' b'gnuplot is a command-driven interactive data/function plotting program. it' b'runs on just about any machine, and is very flexible in terms of supported' b'output devices. the official north american distribution site for the